ENGH 303: Humanities College to Career. 1 credit.
Focuses on career choices and effective self-presentation for soon-to-be graduating students with majors in the humanities. Explores how skills typically learned In humanities majors can be leveraged for a successful transition to post-graduation employment. Offered by English. Limited to three attempts. Equivalent to FRLN 309, HIST 385, PHIL 393, UNIV 420.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

