ENGH 307: English Grammar. 3 credits.
Overview of grammatical structure of English including word classes, phrases, and complex sentences. English grammar analyzed using modern syntactic theory. Students engage in language description through problem solving. Offered by English. Limited to three attempts. Equivalent to LING 307.
Recommended Prerequisite: Satisfaction of University requirements in 100-level English and in Mason Core literature.
Schedule Type: Lecture, Recitation
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

